    "selector_info": "The MRI finding categories reflect diagnostic groups defined after febrile status epilepticus (FSE) based on detailed imaging analysis: 'T2 Hyperintensity' includes cases with definite abnormal T2 signal (graded ≥2 on a 0–4 scale), indicating hippocampal inflammation or injury, strongly linked to hippocampal sclerosis (HS) and mesial temporal lobe epilepsy (MTLE). 'Extrahippocampal Abnormalities' encompass structural issues outside the hippocampus, such as mass lesions, lobar atrophy, or white matter damage, contributing to an intermediate epilepsy risk. 'Dysmorphic Hippocampus' refers to structural irregularities in hippocampal formation, such as malrotation (HIMAL) or nonspecific dysmorphism, defined by visual inspection of shape and symmetry, and associated with moderate risk. 'T2 Norma",
